      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 70: The deactivation runnable aborts whenever push is disabled or the token is null, even if accounts were already deactivated by this background optimization. If the user disables push, the FCM token is cleared, or settings are changed while the app is backgrounded, the recorded accounts can remain inactive until a foreground lifecycle event happens; for long-running background-only use this creates a missed-call/message window. The settings/token gate should be applied before deciding to deactivate, but restoration should still be allowed when the gate becomes false. For example:\n```suggestion\nif (startedActivityCount !\u003d 0) return@Runnable\nif (!mPreferencesService.settings.enablePushNotifications || pushToken \u003d\u003d null) {\n    Log.d(TAG, \"Push unavailable while backgrounded — restoring accounts\")\n    mAccountService.restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()\n    return@Runnable\n}\n```",
