      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 615: restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground() keeps ids forever when the account is disabled or proxy is turned off, but the comment treats those states as possibly transient. For user-driven configuration changes, this preserves a stale restore intent that can reactivate the account later if the user re-enables it or toggles proxy, even though that future state was not background-deactivated. Drop the restore intent for terminal/user configuration changes and only retain ids when the account is temporarily absent during reload if that is a real state here. Suggested direction:\n```suggestion\nval account \u003d mAccountList.firstOrNull { it.accountId \u003d\u003d id }\nwhen {\n    account \u003d\u003d null -\u003e Unit // keep only if account reload can make it reappear\n    account.isEnabled \u0026\u0026 account.isDhtProxyEnabled -\u003e {\n        JamiService.setAccountActive(id, true)\n        backgroundDeactivatedAccounts.remove(id)\n    }\n    else -\u003e backgroundDeactivatedAccounts.remove(id)\n}\n```",
